==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wickedly
<hw>Wick"ed*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a wicked manner; in a
manner, or with motives and designs, contrary to the divine law or the
law of morality; viciously; corruptly; immorally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have sinned, and I have done <qex>wickedly</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>2
Sam. xxiv. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wickedness</ent>⟦br⟧
